==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Clotted
<hw>Clot"ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Composed of clots or
clods; having the quality or form of a clot; sticky; slimy; foul.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>clotted</xex> glebe.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>J.
Philips.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When lust . . . ⟦br⟧
Lets in defilement to the inward parts,⟦br⟧
The soul grows <qex>clotted</qex> by contagion.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clotter</ent>⟦br⟧
